--lua local TIME_DISPLAY_UID = 198818
local function updateTimeDisplay(content) local timeDisplay = getObjectForUID(TIME_DISPLAY_UID) if timeDisplay then timeDisplay.content = content print("Time updated: " .. content) else print("Error: Object UID " .. TIME_DISPLAY_UID .. " not found.") end end
local function fetchUTCTime() local utcNow = os.time(os.date("!*t")) local beijingNow = utcNow + 8 * 3600 local utcTime = os.date("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S CST", beijingNow)
updateTimeDisplay(utcTime) end
if IS_SERVER then print("Script is running on the server. Initializing UTC time updates...")
createTimer(fetchUTCTime, 1.0, true) fetchUTCTime() else print("Script is running on client. No action taken.") end

--lua local TIME_DISPLAY_UID = 197905
local function updateTimeDisplay(content) local timeDisplay = getObjectForUID(TIME_DISPLAY_UID) if timeDisplay then timeDisplay.content = content print("Time updated: " .. content) else print("Error: Object UID " .. TIME_DISPLAY_UID .. " not found.") end end
local function fetchUTCTime()
local utcTime = os.date("!%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S UTC")
updateTimeDisplay(utcTime) end
if IS_SERVER then print("Script is running on the server. Initializing UTC time updates...")
createTimer(fetchUTCTime, 1.0, true) fetchUTCTime() else print("Script is running on client. No action taken.") end

--lua
function onUserUsedObject(av : Avatar, ob : Object) showMessageToUser("Hi " .. av.name .. ", Welcome!", av) end

--lua
function onUserTouchedObject(avatar, ob)
local t = os.date("*t") local seconds = t.sec
local p = avatar.pos
if seconds % 2 == 0 then --dark p.x = 260.0 p.y = 355.8 p.z = 1.68 else -- light p.x = 209.8 p.y = 369.3 p.z = 1.67
end
avatar.pos = p end

--lua
-- Function to teleport the user when touching the object function onUserTouchedObject(avatar, ob) print("Portal activated! Attempting teleport to denshipilov/metasiberia")
-- Check if avatar and pos exist if avatar and avatar.pos then -- Set coordinates local p = avatar.pos p.x = 0.3 p.y = 5.2 p.z = 1.67 avatar.pos = p
-- Attempt to set orientation (heading=86.8), if supported if avatar.rotation then avatar.rotation = { x = 0, y = 86.8, z = 0 } -- Assuming rotation takes a table print("Orientation set: rotation.y = 86.8") elseif avatar.yaw then avatar.yaw = 86.8 print("Orientation set: yaw = 86.8") else print("Orientation not supported (no rotation or yaw)") end
-- World change placeholder (not implemented in Lua, likely set in editor) local targetWorld = "denshipilov/metasiberia" print("Warning: World change not implemented. Set world to " .. targetWorld .. " in Substrata editor or check API.")
print("User teleported to coordinates: x=" .. p.x .. ", y=" .. p.y .. ", z=" .. p.z .. ", target world: " .. targetWorld) else print("Error: avatar or pos unavailable") end end
